  "vulnerability_information": "**Description:**\ni recently found a bunch of FOUO documents, ranging from multiple websites, owned by the U.S government. Most do not seem to hold much Sensitive information (just election stuff along with Cyber threats and new malware).\n\nBut one of the files, had a persons passport on it, including the FIRST 4 pages.\n\ni have sent a link to this specific Document, seeing as the others stemmed from multiple websites and did not seem at all sensitive.\n\nAlso, a website known as the Distributed Denial of Secrets is leaking \"Secret\" u.s documents, regarding stolen Military vehicle number pates. I believe this website may be in possession of other Secret u.s documentation. (But am unsure whether third party sites are in scope: if not, i would be happy to help te U.S hunt down these files on that site, if you have any other means of contact.)\n\n\n\n## References\n█████████\n\n## Impact\n\nAccess to someone's private passport, complete with their address, DOB and personal information.\n\n## System Host(s)\n██████████\n\n## Affected Product(s) and Version(s)\n\n\n## CVE Numbers\n\n\n## Steps to Reproduce\n1)enter this into google:   intitle:FOUO filetype:pdf\n2) go to second page, final result\n\n\nurl to file:\n███\n\n## Suggested Mitigation/Remediation Actions\nremove this from google search engine.\n\n",
